      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Draft ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In reply to yr letter of the 8th Instant ¶ See M to H. Ord, 8 November 1878. ¶  ¶ addressed to His Excellency the Governor asking to be allowed to select a portion of land lying betwe...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.11.26a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Roger Goldsworthy</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Colonial Secretary's Office, acc. 527, no. 345/5, State Records Office of Western Australia, Perth.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter dated<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and correspondent inferred<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from the notes on the file and from M to R. Goldsworthy, 26 December 1878.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 25 November 1878, C. D. Price minuted: 'The land asked for by Baron Von Mueller is the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Perth Commonage</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— it is the only Crown Land adjacent to Perth and the Fremantle &amp; Perth Railway will run through it'. On 26 November 1878, Goldsworthy minuted: 'This will, I suppose, be the reply to Baron Von Müeller'. There is a further minute with the same date, probably by the Governor, H. Ord: 'Write to the Baron to this effect'.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Draft</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to yr letter of the 8th Instant<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to H. Ord, 8 November 1878.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>addressed to His Excellency the Governor asking to be allowed to select a portion of land lying between Perth &amp; Fremantle on behalf of Mr Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to whom the right of selection of 2000 acres was given in appreciation of his services as an Explorer I have the honor in reply to inform you that the land in question is set apart as Commonage for the city of Perth &amp; cannot be granted —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am likewise instructed to acquaint you that there are not in the country lying between Perth &amp; Fremantle any blocks of land to the extent of 2000 acres available.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">[...]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is no signature on the file copy.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Müeller</p>
